SIMPLE: heteronereis
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heteronereis
<hw>Het`e*ro*ne*re"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Hetero-</er>, and <er>Nereis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
free-swimming, dimorphic, sexual form of certain species of
Nereis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In this state the head and its appendages are changed in
form, the eyes become very large; more or less of the parapodia are
highly modified by the development of finlike lobes, and branchial
lamell⟦ae⟧, and their set⟦ae⟧ become longer and bladelike.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heteronomous</ent>⟦br⟧
